      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.5-figure1",
      "type": "figure",
      "section": "26.5",
      "text": "Figure 26.5-1A (Continued). Basic wind speeds for Risk Category I buildings and other structures.\n\nWind speed map of the United States showing basic wind speeds for Risk Category I buildings and other structures. The map displays contour lines with wind speed values ranging from 95 mph to 170 mph across different regions. Notable features include: higher wind speeds along the Atlantic and Gulf coasts (130-170 mph), moderate speeds in the interior (95-120 mph), and special wind regions marked with dotted patterns. The map includes Alaska in the upper left corner showing speeds of 100-107 mph. Numerical values are shown both in mph and m/s in parentheses (e.g., 95(42), 100(45), etc.). Special wind regions are indicated with a dotted pattern and explained in the legend.",
